==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''[[accubatio]]'', for ''[[accubitio]]'', from ''[[accubare]]'' to [[recline]]; ''ad'' + ''[[cubare]]'' to lie down. See [[accumb]].

===Pronunciation===
'''ac*cu-ba*tion'''
AAH-keoo-BEI-shun

===Noun===
'''accubation'''

# The act or [[posture]] of [[reclining]] on a [[couch]], as [[practiced]] by the ancients at meals.

